<p>I am using html2pdf in my Yii application to generate Pdf's, This is my code</p>  <p>Some 'Hindi' or 'Tamil' words are need to show in the pdf.</p>  <p>How can I get this?</p>  <p>sample code and generated Pdf are below, it shows either '?' or squares</p>  <pre><code>    $html2pdf = Yii::app()-&gt;ePdf-&gt;HTML2PDF();     $html2pdf = new HTML2PDF('L', 'A4', 'en');     $html2pdf-&gt;setDefaultFont('freesans');     $html2pdf-&gt;WriteHTML($this-&gt;renderPartial('attentancepdf', array(), true));     $html2pdf-&gt;Output($batch_name); </code></pre>  <p><a href="http://i.stack.imgur.com/t6KDM.jpg" rel="nofollow"><img src="http://i.stack.imgur.com/t6KDM.jpg" alt="**output**"></a></p>